<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">varthdadur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">...The number of bone chips I turned in to become non-kos in Cabilis!  Actually since I turn in 160 at a time (full 8 slot pack) before checking my faction each time it could be anywhere from 6,080 - 6,240 bone chips.  At that point I could run through all of Cabilis except for the necro guild.  I could also bank.  No more using invis potions.<P>I turned in another 1,200 or so and now I am apprehensive to all but the necro guild.  This allows me to buy/sell at merchants.  Cabilis is a great zone for doing trade skills but so is Shar Vahl so that's not that important anymore.<P>I'm bound at the fire pot room so its real easy for me to port to Cabilis and run through to any Kunark zone.  (Cabilis is right in the middle of everything making it a nice hub)<P>Do I recommend you doing it?  Not really!  Unless you are a faction nut like me or really bored for a week, I wouldn't attempt it.  If you do use the fire pot room or find yourself wanting to run through the city for some reason then just use whatever form of invis you have.<P>~Gratz me!~<P>Ps.  I'm a Dwarven cleric so I worship Brell.  Some guides I read stated that the shaman guild will still be KOS because of religion differences but I this is false.  I hailed and /conned the shaman GM and he was apprehensive too.<P>------------------<BR>Baron Varth L60 High Priest<BR>Mogwa L51 Monk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Quotison</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/cheer<P>Now go spread the word of Brell amongst all the lizards!<P>------------------<BR><B><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42628" TARGET=_blank>Quotison Iachwer</A></B><BR>51st Level Vicar of Brell<BR><B><A HREF="http://www.knightseternity.com" TARGET=_blank> &lt;Knights of Eternity&gt;</A></B> <BR>Tarew Marr Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ukerric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The "you will remain KOS" rumor is an artefact of the - now very old - way faction adjustments used to be.<P>It used to be that, once you had maxed the first adjustement (in negative or positive) of a quest/kill, the other faction adjustements were displayed, but not applied.<P>So, once you maxed your Legion of Cabilis from that quest, you didn't get adjustments with the other Cabilis factions. Trick was, unless you were a rogue, agnostic, or worshipping Cazic Thule, you need to get enough faction from kills to get dubious with the Legion of Cabilis for turning in the chips, and the required adjustement put you close enough to max Legion faction that you would get there before the rest of the factions went un-KOS.<P>(there was still a way to get faction after that, as the merchants are limited to dubious faction, regardless of real factions, so you could do the curscale skin quest with a merchant, as the factions weren't in the same order).<P>All these problems went away when faction adjustements were fixed and you got the "cannot become any better/worse" message without locking the rest of the faction.<P>NB: If you want to be at peace with the necro guild, go slaughter Iksar Bandits now.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">blueninja</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just out of curiosity, how the hell did you get that many bone chips?!?!  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Picklesworth,<BR>level 51 high elf cleric on Fennin ro server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kornaena</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have been Max legion for a long time.  Still been turning bone chips and getting Crusader raises.  I am dubious to some crusaders and threatening to others atm.  I went from scowls to these factions after I had maxxed Legion faction.  2000 bone chips and counting.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">varthdadur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Ukerric:<BR><B>The "you will remain KOS" rumor is an artefact of the - now very old - way faction adjustments used to be.<BR></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>The faction guide was written after this change and specifically stated how the old way of faction worked.  I can't remember where I read it but I know that I found the link on these boards somewhere.  The person that wrote it up was a dwarven paladin, I remember.<P>/shrug<P>Oh and I got most of the bone chips from Kurns tower only a zone away from the quest person.  Tons and tons of skeletons and they often drop up to 3 per kill.  I'd clear the first and upper floors with my monk while auctioning for stacks at 5pp each.  I saw a few other people doing the same thing too...at least I left some mobs up for the lowbies...sheesh people!<P>Another spot I tried was the newbie grounds in paineel.  Lots of decaying skeletons.  So many that I rarely was able to kill them all.  I would cast sense undead to target them easy.  The problem there was I had weird lag all the time and the skeletons often dropped no bone chips at all.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Baron Varth L60 High Priest<BR>Mogwa L51 Monk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mahtan Honorshield</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">There was a way to continue to get faction from killing mobs after you'd bottomed the main faction out. If you died to a mob on that faction, you got +200 (not 100% sure on the number here) in faction and could start killing them again for a little while.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">teamnoir</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The last time my chanter tried illusion: iksar in cabalis, she was able to walk through the streets, so long as she avoided shaman.<P>This would have been about February of this year.  she is agnostic.<P>Aidal</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
